message.content:
cs.SD, cs.CV, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper focuses on developing an approach for dense semantic labeling of sound-making objects purely based on binaural sounds. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper leverages the co-existence of visual and audio cues for supervision transfer and proposes a multi-tasking network for boosting overall performance. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a novel sensor setup and records a new audio-visual dataset of street scenes with eight professional binaural microphones and a 360-degree camera. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper proposes a novel task on Spatial Sound Super-resolution to increase the spatial resolution of sounds and formulates the three tasks into one end-to-end trainable multi-tasking network. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): Although not the main focus, the paper mentions the release of data and code to facilitate research in this new direction, which could be relevant to the social and information networks sub-category.
